2 SENATE BILL 748
1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
3 Article – Health – General
4 18–110.
5 The Department, in partnership with the Department of Aging, the Virginia I. Jones
6 Alzheimer’s Disease and Related Disorders DEMENTIAS Council, and the Greater
7 Maryland Chapter of the Alzheimer’s Association, shall incorporate information into
8 relevant public health outreach programs administered by the Department to:
9 (1) Educate health care providers regarding:
10 (i) The importance of early detection and timely diagnosis of
11 cognitive impairment;
12 (ii) Validated assessment tools for the detection and diagnosis of
13 cognitive impairment;
14 (iii) The value of a Medicare annual wellness visit or other annual
15 physical for an individual at least 65 years old for cognitive health; [and]
16 (iv) The Medicare care planning billing code for individuals with
17 cognitive impairment; and
18 (V) TREATMENTS APPROVED BY THE FOOD AND DRUG
19 ADMINISTRATION FOR ALZHEIMER’S DISEASE AND RELATED DEMENTIAS,
20 INCLUDING RELEVANT INFORMATION ON TREATMENT USE AND OUTCOMES; AND
21 (2) Increase PUBLIC understanding and awareness of:
22 (i) The early warning signs of Alzheimer’s disease and [other types
23 of dementia] RELATED DEMENTIAS;
24 (ii) The value of early detection [and], diagnosis, AND TREATMENT
25 of Alzheimer’s disease and [other types of dementia] RELATED DEMENTIAS; and
26 (iii) How to reduce the risk of cognitive decline, particularly among
27 individuals in Black and Latino communities who are at greater risk of developing
28 Alzheimer’s disease and [other types of dementia] RELATED DEMENTIAS; AND
29 (IV) TREATMENTS APPROVED BY THE U.S. FOOD AND DRUG
30 ADMINISTRATION FOR ALZHEIMER’S DISEASE AND RELATED DEMENTIAS AND
31 RELEVANT INFORMATION ON TREATMENT USE AND OUTCOMES, INCLUDING
32 INFORMATION RELATED TO TREATMENT OUTCOMES BASED ON BIOLOGICAL SEX.

