1 18–111.
2 (A) THE DEPARTMENT, IN COLLABORATION WITH THE STATE–DESIGNATED
3 HEALTH INFORMATION EXCHANGE, SHALL ESTABLISH AND MAINTAIN A PUBLICLY
4 ACCESSIBLE WEBSITE THAT INCLUDES IN A DOWNLOADABLE FORMAT THE
5 FOLLOWING INFORMATION:
6 (1) THE PREVALENCE OF ALZHEIMER’S DISEASE AND RELATED
7 DEMENTIAS IN THE STATE;
8 (2) THE HOSPITALIZATION RATE RELATED TO ALZHEIMER’S DISEASE
9 AND RELATED DEMENTIAS; AND
10 (3) TO THE EXTENT POSSIBLE, THE PREVALENCE AND
11 HOSPITALIZATION RATE OF ALZHEIMER’S DISEASE AND RELATED DEMENTIAS
12 DISAGGREGATED BASED ON:
13 (I) AGE, INCLUDING AGE OF DIAGNOSIS;
14 (II) SEX;
15 (III) RACE;
16 (IV) ETHNICITY; AND
17 (V) NUMBER OF CASES BY COUNTY;
18 (VI) CO–OCCURRENCE OF DOWN SYNDROME (TRISOMY–21);
19 AND
20 (VII) TYPE OF DEMENTIA.
21 (B) THE WEBSITE REQUIRED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION
22 SHALL:
23 (1) INCLUDE THE DATA AVAILABLE FOR THE IMMEDIATELY
24 PRECEDING 5–YEAR PERIOD ENDING SEPTEMBER 30, 2025; AND
25 (2) BE UPDATED ON OR BEFORE JANUARY 1 EACH YEAR, BEGINNING
26 IN 2027, TO INCLUDE ANY NEWLY AVAILABLE DATA.
27 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
28 October 1, 2025.

